==English==
===Etymology===
From Arabic {{ARchar|[[علماء]]}} (‘ulamā’), plural of {{ARchar|[[عالم]]}} (‘ālim) ‘learned one’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈʊləmə/, /ˈu:lɪmə/, /u:ləˈmɑ:/}}

===Noun===
'''ulema''' ''(only in plural or taken as collective plural)''

# The guardians of legal and religious tradition in [[Islam]]; [[clerics]].
#:*'''2000''': For the time being, the faithful must follow their own consciences and learn to distinguish good from evil by themselves, instead fo relying on the '''''ulema'''''. — Karen Armstrong, ''The Battle for God'' (Harper 2004, p. 131)

